benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/renameKey - Update a bundle externalKey

covered: Valid Request: Scenario TC01 covers successful update with correct headers and body.

Error Handling: Scenarios TC02 (missing header), TC03 (malformed bundleId), TC04 (non-existent bundle), TC06 (missing body), TC07 (malformed JSON), TC08 (missing externalKey), TC12 (unauthorized), TC13 (service unavailable), TC15 (no bundles in system), TC16 (large payload), TC17 (concurrent updates), TC18 (regression with problematic externalKey), TC19 (special characters), TC20 (spaces), TC21 (extra headers), TC22 (backward compatibility), TC23 (response time), TC24 (accessibility) cover a broad range of error and edge cases.
Additional Validations: TC05 (externalKey conflict) and TC09 (extra fields) cover conflict and extra data scenarios.
Edge Cases: TC10 (long externalKey), TC11 (empty externalKey) cover length and validation edge cases.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with multiple bundles.
Authorization: No explicit tests for invalid or expired tokens beyond TC12.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests to test throttling.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Response Time Under Load: Only TC23 mentions response time, but no load testing scenarios are included.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination to verify handling of large datasets and list retrievals.
Include explicit authorization tests with invalid/expired tokens to ensure security.
Implement rate limiting tests to verify system stability under high request volume.
Add scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behaviors.
Include performance/load testing scenarios to measure response times under stress.
